---
import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
import GlowLineSeparator from '@/components/ui/separator/GlowLineSeparator.astro';
import ArrowSeparator from '@/components/ui/separator/ArrowSeparator.astro';
const pageTitle = 'About Me';
const pageDescription = 'Learn more about me, my background, and my career.';
---

<Layout title={pageTitle} description={pageDescription} pubDate={new Date()} showHeader={false}>

<br>

<p>
  I'm Caleb, a USAF veteran with over 8 years of experience across military intelligence, cyber operations support, and training leadership, now focused on enterprise technology and digital transformation.
</p>

<p>
  Early in my career, I served as a Persian-Farsi language analyst supporting national-level cyber operations at U.S. Cyber Command, where I developed a security-minded, analytical approach to working in complex technical environments. That experience required translating (literally) ambiguous, highly technical information into insights for decision-makers and operators, which it shaped how I think about risk, access, and cross-functional operations.
</p>

<p>
  Later, in leadership roles overseeing military language training programs, I focused on improving outcomes through process improvement and automation. By modernizing workflows with enterprise cloud productivity and automation platforms, I helped teams operate more efficiently while reinforcing the importance of clear communication between technical and non-technical stakeholders.
</p>

<p>
  I’m currently completing my Master’s in Information Technology with a concentration in cybersecurity while building hands-on experience across cloud infrastructure, security, and automation. I’m transitioning from active duty in November 2026 and pursuing roles focused on modernizing and securing enterprise technology environments.
</p>

<p>
  Outside of work, I enjoy being in the mountains hiking, backpacking, and skiing, traveling to explore new cultures and cuisines, spending time with my fiancée and our dogs, and gaming with friends.
</p>
        <GlowLineSeparator />
</Layout>
